DIV2.P:
164. Jan. 11. My Wifes Sister Mrs. Mary
 fell ill of an Ague, and having
had five its;

Sept. 3. I returned to London from Mr. Lilly's.
Mrs. Dorcas Pagitt, Wife to Justinian Pagitt, Es{que}
was buried.

Apr. 1. My Wife fell ill of Rheumatism;
it began in her left Ancle, then into her left
Knee and right Toe.
